	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Gun Nac is really good.  Feels more like a 16 bit era game, with the options and variety of powerups it gives you.  5 types of guns with several upgrade levels, 5 types of screen-clearing bombs, change your ship movement speed anytime you want with Select(!), even change whether speed has priority or displaying every sprite has priority.
<br />
<br />Plus it has pretty good graphics.  Just a nice solid game with a fair difficulty curve.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v164/UncleSporky/gunnac.gif" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />Another shooter I enjoyed on the NES was Stinger, which alternates between side scrolling and overhead levels and has strange and fun enemies such as watermelons and coat hangers.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


